</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 1em 0;">To illustrate the point, Urban wrote up a thought experiment:&=
nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 1em 0;">Imagine that you got in a time machine back to 1750, grab=
bed someone alive then, and then brought them back to the present to show h=
im around and watch his reactions. Everything we take for granted -- cars, =
tall buildings, iPhones, live sports broadcasts, recorded music, Google Map=
s -- would blow his mind in such a major way that he wouldn&#8217;t just be=
 shocked, he might actually <strong>die</strong>.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"colo=
r: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">If that=
 guy wanted to pay it forward and kill someone with shock by bringing them =
to 1750, he couldn&#8217;t just go back ~250 years and grab someone from 15=
00. 1750 and 1500 are too similar. There would be some new things, but noth=
ing that would kill the 1500s guy. To get the same effect, Urban guesses th=
at he would have to pick someone up who lived around ~12,000 BC, before the=
 First Agricultural Revolution. <em>That</em> guy, in turn, couldn&#8217;t =
just go back 12,000 years to 24,000 BC, &#8220;he&#8217;d have to go back o=
ver 100,000 years and get someone he could show fire and language to for th=
e first time.&#8221;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">He called the amount of time you&#8217;d h=
ave to go ahead to be shocked enough at the world to die a <strong>Die Prog=
ress Unit (DPU)</strong>. The DPU is a colorful illustration of an idea fro=
m futurist Ray Kurzweil, the author of <em>The Singularity is Near</em>: th=
e <strong>Law of Accelerating Returns</strong>.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color:=
 #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><strong>T=
he Law of Accelerating Returns states that the rate of change of progress a=
ccelerates because humans can use the technology at their disposal to progr=
ess faster than previous generations could without the technology.&nbsp;</s=
trong></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 1em 0;">This is demonstrably true, using DPUs or actual numbers,=
